Alerts:
Alert is a pop up messsage takes complete focus of our main page(main page is disabled) that we are working on
We cannot proceed until it is handle the alert.

3 Types of Alerts
Web Based alerts/html alerts= we can simply inspect and perform actions( we don't need to switch part of our main page)

JavaScript alerts/browser Alerts= we can handle these alerts by using switch to method, we cannot inspect

Windows based alerts= we cannot handle with selenium

Types of JavaScript alerts:
1.Simple Alert-click oK
2.confirmation alert= either cancel or click ok
3.prompt Alert=enter text and then click ok

To handle JS alerts we only have 4 methods
1.accept()-click ok
2.dismiss()-clicks cancel
3.getText()
4.sendKeys()

To handle Authentication alerts we need to pass username and password in url
username:password@
"https://admin:admin@the-internet.herokuapp.com/basic_auth";
admin:admin@

Frames are separate and independent windows that allow developers to present different webpages in one
Frames:
Separate independent window inside our webpage, an html inside another html
frame is a separate independent window in our webpage
frames allow dev to represent multiple view on a page. a webpage inside our main page a separate nested window

3 ways to interact with frames:
1.by index
2.by name or ID
3.by webElement

in alerts-switch manually to alert and switch automatically back
in frames-switch manually to a frame and switch manually back to the main page

interview Q
HOW DO YOU HANDLE ALERTS
R. we handle alerts by using alert interface


